# Navigation Rules (go_router)

## Requirements
- Use GoRouter with typed routes (go_router_builder)
- Support deep linking for all public routes
- Auth guards via redirect, not widget-level checks
- Each feature declares its own route subtree
- Routes assembled in packages/routing

## Patterns
- Use context.go() for declarative navigation
- Use context.push() only when back-stack is needed
- Extra data via path/query parameters, NOT via extra (not type-safe)
- Nested navigation via StatefulShellRoute for tab-based layouts

## Forbidden
- Navigator.push/pop directly
- MaterialPageRoute construction
- Passing complex objects via GoRouter extra parameter
- Navigation logic inside widgets (use redirects)
